I have intrinsically always believed in the lack of control over another, like I have mentioned very many years ago, but I did not know then why that is the case â€“ I only knew it felt right.

It is only recently that I came to the conscious conclusion that exercising control over anotherâ€™s freedom is not conducive for relationships between adults. As sentient beings, we are always changing, hopefully for the better, and limiting my very own partner makes zero sense to me. Instead, I turned inwards, focusing on myself in order to become a better person for the sake of myself and for you. Nobody else is responsible for my being after all â€“ I am the protagonist in my own story.

Accordingly, this is one way I express my love. I have always chosen, and will continue to choose to, love you more regardless of the choices you make.

Just like before, I again stress that I do not expect you share my beliefs â€“ we are distinct individuals after all, and I absolutely do not wish for us to become one and the same.

This brings us to the concepts of Trust and Faith. In the context of relationships, to Trust and to have Faith is the healthy way of dealing with oneâ€™s own insecurities. On the other hand, to deal with the insecurities by exercising control over another is simply dumping the problem onto someone else. The distinction is that the former has the potential to lead to resolution and growth, while the latter is stagnation and possibly even regression and abuse.

We are both aware of the insecurities you have, and I have always been immensely proud of you. The courage you have shown by Trusting and having Faith time and time again is something that I cannot even imagine. Please continue to be brave, and perhaps one day you will no longer be bound by your fears. The two of us are responsible for our own relationship, and again I promise you that nothing else will come between us.

I hope too, that you can turn inwards to understand yourself better. I know feelings is not your strong suit, but I am always here to help you in your journey â€“ the protagonist in your very own life story.

Just like joy and happiness, there will also always be challenges and difficulties ahead. With utmost conviction, I believe that our relationship will continue to flourish regardless.

Yours truly,
Husband <This message was edited>
